esumable: it validates cached `.ply` and `.swc` files, treats zero-byte/malformed cache entries as invalid, writes fetched assets atomically, supports forced refetch and optional skeleton hard-fail mode, and records structured per-asset provenance with `fetch_status` values like `cache_hit`, `fetched`, `skipped`, and `failed`. The manifest contract in [geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/geometry_contract.py#L111) now stores that `raw_asset_provenance` and can load/merge existing records so rerunning fetches or later processed-asset builds does not clobber prior state.\\n\\nThe CLI in [02_fetch_meshes.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py#L36) now accepts `--refetch-meshes`, `--refetch-skeletons`, and `--require-skeletons`, writes per-root provenance into the manifest, reports aggregate cache-hit/fetch/failure counts, and preserves existing bundle records on reruns. [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py#L64) now preserves the raw-fetch provenance when processed assets are built. I also added regression coverage in [tests/test_mesh_pipeline_fetch.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_mesh_pipeline_fetch.py#L44), plus manifest/integration assertions in [tests/test_geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_geometry_contract.py#L52) and [tests/test_config_paths.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_config_paths.py#L72). Config examples were updated with the new knobs in [config/local.yaml](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/config/local.yaml) and [config/visual_subset.example.yaml](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/config/visual_subset.example.yaml).\\n\\nVerified with `make test` and `.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_mesh_pipeline_fetch -v`. Both passed.\"}}\n./agent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-002_Make_raw_geometry_ingestion_cache-aware_resumable_and_provenance-rich/stdout.jsonl:121:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_26\",\"type\":\"todo_list\",\"items\":[{\"text\":\"Extend geometry fetch library for cache validation, refetch controls, and per-asset provenance\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Wire CLI/config controls and manifest records through scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Add regression tests for cache reuse, refetch, corrupted cache, and skeleton failure\",\"completed\":true},{\"text\":\"Run requested verification commands and summarize results\",\"completed\":true}]}}\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:164:def describe_skeleton(path: str | Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:215:    skeleton_adj = sp.csr_matrix(\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:219:    component_summary = _component_summary(skeleton_adj)\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:247:    skeleton_summary: dict[str, Any],\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:252:    raw_skeleton_path: str | Path,\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:273:            \"raw_skeleton_path\": str(raw_skeleton_path),\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:288:            \"skeleton\": skeleton_summary,\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:314:        \"raw_skeleton_path\": str(raw_skeleton_path),\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:458:            \"raw_skeleton_available\": bool(descriptor_payload[\"representations\"][\"skeleton\"][\"available\"]),\n./src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py:465:        \"raw_skeleton_available\": bool(descriptor_payload[\"representations\"][\"skeleton\"][\"available\"]),\n./Makefile:15:.PHONY: help bootstrap verify registry select meshes assets preview coupling-inspect operator-qa simu